    "\"These orange cloaks,\" one answered, \"are of lead, and of such thickness are they, that the weights thus cause the scales that balance them to creak.",
    "We Jovial Friars were, and Bolognese; I, Catalàn, and Loderingo he, by name, and chosen by thy town together, as one alone is usually called, to keep its peace; and such we were, as still in the Gardingo's neighborhood appears.\"",
    "\"O friars,\" I began, \"your evil deeds ...\"",
