    "Therefore get up! O'ercome thy troubled breath with that soul-energy, which wins all fights, unless it sink beneath its body's weight! A longer stairway must be climbed; 't is not enough that these stairs have been left; if, then, thou understand me, let it profit thee.\"",
    "I thereupon arose, and showed myself better equipped with breath than I had felt, and said: \"Go on, for I am strong and bold!\"",
