    "On had I moved, and in my Teacher's steps was following willingly, and both of us were showing now how light of step we were, when \"Downward turn thine eyes!\" he said to me, \"Well will it be, to calm thee on thy way, that thou shouldst see the bed thy soles are treading.\"",
