    "And as the sun availeth not the blind, so to the shades, whereof I spoke just now, the sky's light willeth not to grant itself; because an iron band runs through, and sews the eyelids of them all, as with wild hawks one does, since otherwise they 'd not keep still.",
    "To me it seemed an outrage that, unseen, I should see others, as I walked along; I therefore turned to my wise Counselor.",
