    "Between the third hour's close and day's beginning as much as is apparent of the sphere, which like a child is ever given to play, so much now of its course toward evening seemed remaining to the sun; 't was vespers there, and midnight here; and fully on the face its rays were striking us, because the Mount had so been circled by us, that we now were going on directly toward the West; when, far more blindingly than e'er before, I felt my forehead overcome by splendor, and was bewildered by these unknown things; over my eyebrows, hence, I raised my hands, and made myself the screen which, filing off, tempers excessive light in what is seen.",
